                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "HUF (Hindu Undivided Family)",
                "description": "A family business structure unique to Indian law; recognised as a separate person under Section 2(31) of the Income Tax Act; applicable to Hindu, Sikh, Jain and Buddhist families; the Karta manages the HUF; coparceners include all family members with birthright in HUF property including daughters since 2005."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Karta",
                "description": "The manager of the HUF; traditionally the eldest male coparcener, but since Sujata Sharma vs Manu Gupta (2016) and the 2005 amendment, women can also be Karta."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Coparceners",
                "description": "Members of the HUF with birthright in HUF property; since the Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act 2005 (effective 9 September 2005), daughters are coparceners with equal rights as sons."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act 2005",
                "description": "The watershed legislation that gave daughters equal coparcenary rights as sons in HUF property; effective 9 September 2005; applies retrospectively except where a disposition or partition occurred before 20 December 2004."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Family Constitution / Charter",
                "description": "A non-binding governance document codifying decision rights, dividend policy, employment criteria, conflict resolution and exit conditions; not legally enforceable but operationally critical; translated into legally binding shareholders' agreement, voting agreements and individual wills."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Private Family Trust",
                "description": "A trust established under the Indian Trusts Act 1882 where the settlor transfers assets to trustees who hold and manage them for the benefit of family beneficiaries; can be discretionary or specific (determinate)."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Family Settlement Deed",
                "description": "A bona fide arrangement among family members to settle disputes regarding family property; judicially recognised as not constituting a transfer for capital gains under the Income Tax Act per K.K. Modi and subsequent Supreme Court rulings."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Income Tax Act 2025",
                "description": "The new direct tax statute effective 1 April 2026; replaces the Income Tax Act 1961; 536 sections across 23 chapters; tax rates and slabs unchanged; Previous Year and Assessment Year both replaced with Tax Year."
            },
            {
                "@type": "DefinedTerm",
                "name": "Section 56(2)(x) Income Tax Act",
                "description": "Receipt of property without consideration above INR 50,000 from a non-relative is taxable as income from other sources; relatives defined restrictively in the Explanation."
            },
