<!-- SECTION 15A: LEGAL FRAMEWORK -->
<section class="content-section">
    <div class="content-container">
        <div class="text-content">
            <h2 class="section-title">Legal and Compliance Framework</h2>
            <div class="content-text">
                
                <p><strong>HUF Governing Law:</strong> Hindu Law (uncodified); Hindu Succession Act 1956 read with Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act 2005 (Section 6 - daughters as equal coparceners effective 9 September 2005). Pre-20-December-2004 partitions or dispositions protected by the proviso to Section 6.</p>
                <p><strong>HUF Taxation:</strong> Income Tax Act 2025 (effective 1 April 2026) - Section 2(31) defines person to include HUF; HUF taxed separately at individual slab rates; basic exemption INR 3 lakh under new regime; deductions under equivalent of Section 80C, 80D, 80G available (renumbered under ITA 2025).</p>
                <p><strong>Family Operating Entity:</strong> Companies Act 2013 - Pvt Ltd via SPICe+ on MCA21 v3; LLP Act 2008 - LLP via FiLLiP; Section 43 Companies Act 2013 - differential voting rights for control retention; Companies (Share Capital and Debentures) Rules 2014.</p>
                <p><strong>Private Family Trust:</strong> Indian Trusts Act 1882; Section 17 Indian Registration Act 1908 - mandatory registration where immovable property in trust corpus; trustee's duties under Section 11 to Section 30 Indian Trusts Act.</p>
                <p><strong>Family Settlement:</strong> Judicially recognised under multiple Supreme Court rulings (K.K. Modi vs K.N. Modi 1998; Kale vs Deputy Director of Consolidation 1976); bona fide family settlements treated as not constituting a transfer for capital gains under Section 47 read with Income Tax Act 2025.</p>
                <p><strong>Wills:</strong> Indian Succession Act 1925 (Christians, Parsis, Jews); Hindu Succession Act 1956 Section 30 (Hindu testamentary disposition); Muslim law for Muslims (1/3 testamentary disposition limit without consent); registration optional under Section 18 Indian Registration Act 1908 for safekeeping.</p>
                <p><strong>Inheritance / Estate Tax:</strong> NONE - Estate Duty Act 1953 abolished in 1985; no estate, inheritance or generational-skipping tax in India.</p>
                <p><strong>Section 56(2)(x), Section 64, Section 47:</strong> Renumbered equivalents under ITA 2025; substantive rules unchanged - gift treatment, clubbing and family settlement exemptions all carry through.</p>
                <p><strong>SEBI Takeover (for Listed Family Businesses):</strong> SEBI (Substantial Acquisition of Shares and Takeovers) Regulations 2011 - Regulation 30 disclosure on promoter group changes; Regulation 29 intra-promoter transfers; Regulation 10 exemptions.</p>
                <p><strong>Authority for source verification:</strong> Income Tax e-filing portal at <a href="https://www.incometax.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">incometax.gov.in</a>, MCA21 v3 at <a href="https://www.mca.gov.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">mca.gov.in</a> and India Code (statutes) at <a href="https://www.indiacode.nic.in" target="_blank" rel="noopener">indiacode.nic.in</a>.</p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

