                <p>Three timing considerations matter for family business registration. First, the <strong>Income Tax Act 2025 transition</strong> - effective 1 April 2026, all family business taxation moves to the new Act; HUF setups, gift planning under Section 56(2)(x) and family settlement under Section 47 should be reviewed against the new framework. Second, the <strong>Hindu Succession (Amendment) Act 2005</strong> - any older succession plan based on the pre-2005 position is legally vulnerable; rectification through partition deeds, family settlement deeds or supplementary documents should be prioritised before disputes arise.</p>
